<h1>Problem 1698 - 2023 CAPS-Match, P5 of 6 , G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be an acute-angled triangle with orthocenter \(H\). Let \(D\) be the foot of
the altitude from \(A\) to the line \(BC\). Let \(T\) be a point on the circle with diameter
\(AH\) such that this circle is internally tangent to the circumcircle of triangle \(BDT\).
Let \(N\) be the midpoint of segment \(AH\). Prove that \(BT \perp CN\).</p>
